Description: Intact pottery transport amphora. 'Torpedo' jar. Dipinto inscription on body.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Naukratis, Well A (= Hogarth site 36)
Curator's comments: Excavated from a well by Hogarth in 1899 and said to be given to Bulak Museum in Cairo, although this object was not found registered in Cairo, Egyptian Museum (Edgar 1905, 123-5, Fig.3). The collection of pottery from this well was dated by von Bissing to 525-323BC (Edgar 1905, 124-5). As there is no personal name attested beginning with this trio of letters, the text is probably a more complex form of abbreviation.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.076)
Exhibition history: Thought to be stored in Cairo, Egyptian Museum
